articles.title: Remote Australian town looking for doctor offers $400,000 salary, free rent - CBS News
articles.description: The remote Australia town of Julia Creek has a population of just 500 and is a seven-hour drive from the nearest major city.
articles.content:
A remote Australian town that will soon lose its only doctor is offering a salary of up to 680,000 Australian dollars, or $428,000, to attract a new candidate.
